      • isSegmentEncoded

        public boolean isSegmentEncoded()
        Description copied from interface: IGroup
        True if this group is encoded as a segment and therefore should have a PMAP.

        Not all groups have PMAPs - only those that are encoded as "segments" in the transfer encoding.

        For sequences...
        "If any instruction of the group needs to allocate a bit in a presence map, each element is represented as a segment in the transfer encoding."

        For other groups...
        "If any instruction of the group needs to allocate a bit in a presence map, the group is represented as a segment in the transfer encoding."

        Specified by:
        isSegmentEncoded in interface IGroup
        Returns:
        True if group has a PMAP.
